## Happy Path — Exact Event Sequence

```
correlation_id = uuid4()   # fixed for entire task chain

Step 1: AgentRuntime.register(AgentDefinition("cole", "planner", "null", ["plan","analyze"], 10000))
  → IdentityService.register_agent("cole", "planner", parent_id=kernel_root_id)
  → MeteringLayer.allocate(cole_id, "ai_tokens", 10000)
  → EventBus.publish(Event(type="agent.registered", payload={agent_id, role, capabilities}))
  → AuditLedger.append(actor="RUNTIME", action="agent_registered", status="SUCCESS")

Step 2: ModuleLoader.load("crm_module")
  → _validate_manifest(): permissions=["db.read","db.write"], events=["customer.created"] ✓
  → _analyze_ast(): no forbidden imports ✓
  → Module.initialize(kernel_ctx)
  → register_module_subscriptions("crm_module", event_bus)  → subscribes to "customer.created"
  → AuditLedger.append(action="module_loaded")

Step 3: EventBus.publish(Event(type="agent.task_submitted", correlation_id=correlation_id))
  → SchemaRegistry validates payload keys present
  → Signature computed and verified
  → Sequence number assigned (monotonic)
  → Orchestrator subscriber receives event

Step 4: Orchestrator.execute(task_spec) — correlation_id=correlation_id
  for step in range(5):  # max_reasoning_steps=5
    step 0:
      PolicyScopeEnforcer.check("planner", "plan") → OK
      NullProvider.generate(prompt, history=[], config) → AIResponse("NULL_PROVIDER_RESPONSE", 0, 0, 0.0, "null")
      MeteringLayer.record(cole_id, "ai_tokens", 0)
      AI action = "complete" → break
  EventBus.publish(Event(type="agent.task_completed", correlation_id=correlation_id,
                         payload={task_id, steps_taken=1, output="NULL_PROVIDER_RESPONSE"}))
  AuditLedger.append(action="agent_task_completed")
  return AgentTaskResult(COMPLETED, steps_taken=1, final_output="NULL_PROVIDER_RESPONSE")

Step 5: ImprovementEngine.propose_patch(Patch(
    patch_id=uuid4(),
    target_module="crm_module",
    unified_diff="--- a/crm.py\n+++ b/crm.py\n...",
    test_vector="tests/test_crm.py -v",
    proposed_by=cole_id,
  ))
  → "crm_module" not in PROTECTED_PATHS ✓
  → unified_diff != "" ✓
  → PolicyEngine.evaluate(cole_id, "propose_improvement") → ALLOW
  → EventBus.publish(improvement.patch_proposed)
  → AuditLedger.append(action="patch_proposed")

Step 6: ImprovementEngine.approve_patch(patch_id, approver_id="kernel_admin_id")
  → Identity(approver).role == "admin" ✓
  → LocalCIGate.run_tests(patch) → CIResult(passed=True, duration_ms=800, output="1 passed")
  → ModuleLoader.hot_swap("crm_module", new_path)
    → backup current
    → load new version
    → Module.healthcheck() → OK
    → AuditLedger.append(action="module_hot_swapped")
  → EventBus.publish(improvement.patch_applied, patch_id, new_version="1.1.0")
  → AuditLedger.append(action="patch_applied")

Step 7: AuditLedger.verify_integrity() → True   # all steps audited, chain unbroken
```

